data.name: Crispy Fried Mackerel with Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Sautéed Green Beans
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously crispy fried mackerel paired with creamy garlic mashed potatoes and vibrant sautéed green beans, perfect for a hearty meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Rinse the mackerel fillets and pat them dry with paper towels.
In a bowl, mix flour, cornstarch, salt, and black pepper. Dredge the mackerel in the mixture until well coated.
Heat oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Fry the mackerel for about 4-5 minutes on each side or until golden brown and crispy. Drain on paper towels.
Peel and chop the potatoes into chunks. Boil them in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes. Drain and return to the pot.
Add minced garlic, butter, and milk to the potatoes. Mash until creamy and season with salt to taste.
Trim the green beans and blanch them in boiling water for about 3 minutes. Drain and sauté in olive oil for 5 minutes until tender but still crisp. Drizzle with lemon juice and toss to coat.
Serve the crispy mackerel alongside garlic mashed potatoes and sautéed green beans. Garnish with fresh parsley.
data.detailedName: Crispy Fried Mackerel with Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Sautéed Green Beans
data.modifiersForBase: Crispy coating with a side of creamy potatoes and sautéed vegetables.
